replies.bodyText:
pollingJob can be null at this point, because it isn't inittialized in the constructor. So, you need to check if it is not null before accessing it: if (pollingJob != null).
But this would result in a compiler warning, as pollingJob is a field and could theoretically be modified by another thread exactly between the null check and the access in the next line.
To mitigate this, you can store pollingJob to a local variable before checking it:
                                                        Future<?> localPollingJob = pollingJob;
                                                        if (localPollingJob != null) {
                                                            localPollingJob.cancel(true);
                                                        }

